<TITLE> SC stays HC order on imam appointment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 15 (bdnews24.com)--The Supreme Court has stayed for four weeks a High Court order that upheld status quo on the appointment of the imam for the Sholakia Eidgah ground, the site of the country's biggest Eid congregation. Justice AK Sinha, the chamber judge of the Appellate Division, made the order on Tuesday on a government petition. Attorney general Mahbubey Alam filed the petition for a freeze on the High Court order. The High Court on Monday ordered maintaining status quo on the appointment of imam. It also asked the government to explain why the decision of appointing Mohammed Farid Uddin Masud and Mohammed Kholilur Rahman instead of imam Abul Khair Mohammad Saifullah is not illegal. The Kishoreganj deputy commissioner on Sept 2 appointed Farid Uddin and Kholilur Rahman, leaving out imam Saifullah. Saifullah filed a writ petition challenging the legality of the action on Monday
